msgctxt "dn34:1.4.7"
msgid ""
"savitakko savicāro samādhi, avitakko vicāramatto immersion, avitakko avicāro "
"samādhi."
msgstr ""
"Immersion with placing the mind and keeping it connected. Immersion without "
"placing the mind, but just keeping it connected. Immersion without placing "
"the mind or keeping it connected."

#. <section class="sutta" id="dn34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn34:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 34"
msgstr "Long Discourses 34"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn34:0.2"
msgid "Dasuttarasutta"
msgstr "Up to Ten"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.272"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Campā on the banks of the Gaggarā "
"Lotus Pond together with a large Saṅgha of five hundred mendicants."

msgctxt "dn34:1.1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "dn34:1.1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "dn34:1.1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.7"
msgid "“Dasuttaraṃ pavakkhāmi,"
msgstr "“I will relate the teachings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.8"
msgid "dhammaṃ nibbānapattiyā;"
msgstr "up to ten for attaining extinguishment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.9"
msgid "Dukkhassantakiriyāya,"
msgstr "for making an end of suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.10"
msgid "sabbaganthappamocanaṃ."
msgstr "the release from all ties."

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.1.11"
msgid "1. Eko dhammo"
msgstr "1. Groups of One"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Eko, āvuso, dhammo bahukāro, eko dhammo bhāvetabbo, eko dhammo pariññeyyo, "
"eko dhammo pahātabbo, eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo, eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo, eko "
"dhammo duppaṭivijjho, eko dhammo uppādetabbo, eko dhammo abhiññeyyo, eko "
"dhammo sacchikātabbo."
msgstr ""
"Reverends, one thing is helpful, one thing should be developed, one thing "
"should be completely understood, one thing should be given up, one thing "
"makes things worse, one thing leads to distinction, one thing is hard to "
"comprehend, one thing should be produced, one thing should be directly "
"known, one thing should be realized."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.2"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo bahukāro?"
msgstr "What one thing is helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.3"
msgid "Appamādo kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "Diligence in skillful qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo bahukāro. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.5"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo bhāvetabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.6"
msgid "Kāyagatāsati sātasahagatā."
msgstr "Mindfulness of the body that is full of pleasure."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo bhāvetabbo. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.8"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo pariññeyyo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.9"
msgid "Phasso sāsavo upādāniyo."
msgstr ""
"Contact, which is accompanied by defilements and is prone to being grasped."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo pariññeyyo. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.273"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.11"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo pahātabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.12"
msgid "Asmimāno."
msgstr "The conceit ‘I am’."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo pahātabbo. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.14"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo?"
msgstr "What one thing makes things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.15"
msgid "Ayoniso manasikāro."
msgstr "Improper attention."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo hānabhāgiyo. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.17"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo?"
msgstr "What one thing leads to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.18"
msgid "Yoniso manasikāro."
msgstr "Proper attention."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.19"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo visesabhāgiyo. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.20"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo duppaṭivijjho?"
msgstr "What one thing is hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.21"
msgid "Ānantariko cetosamādhi."
msgstr "The heart’s immersion of immediate result."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.22"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo duppaṭivijjho. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.23"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo uppādetabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.24"
msgid "Akuppaṃ ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "Unshakable knowledge."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.25"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo uppādetabbo. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.26"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo abhiññeyyo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.27"
msgid "Sabbe sattā āhāraṭṭhitikā."
msgstr "All sentient beings are sustained by food."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.28"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo abhiññeyyo. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.29"
msgid "Katamo eko dhammo sacchikātabbo?"
msgstr "What one thing should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.30"
msgid "Akuppā cetovimutti."
msgstr "The unshakable heart’s release."

msgctxt "dn34:1.2.31"
msgid "Ayaṃ eko dhammo sacchikātabbo. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.32"
msgid ""
"Iti ime dasa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these ten things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.2.33"
msgid "2. Dve dhammā"
msgstr "2. Groups of Two"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.1"
msgid ""
"Dve dhammā bahukārā, dve dhammā bhāvetabbā, dve dhammā pariññeyyā, dve "
"dhammā pahātabbā, dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā, dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā, dve "
"dhammā duppaṭivijjhā, dve dhammā uppādetabbā, dve dhammā abhiññeyyā, dve "
"dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""
"Two things are helpful, two things should be developed, two things should be "
"completely understood, two things should be given up, two things make things "
"worse, two things lead to distinction, two things are hard to comprehend, "
"two things should be produced, two things should be directly known, two "
"things should be realized."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.2"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What two things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.3"
msgid "Sati ca sampajaññañca."
msgstr "Mindfulness and situational awareness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.4"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.5"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.6"
msgid "Samatho ca vipassanā ca."
msgstr "Serenity and discernment."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.7"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.8"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What two things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.9"
msgid "Nāmañca rūpañca."
msgstr "Name and form."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.10"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.274"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.11"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.12"
msgid "Avijjā ca bhavataṇhā ca."
msgstr "Ignorance and craving for continued existence."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.13"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.14"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What two things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.15"
msgid "Dovacassatā ca pāpamittatā ca."
msgstr "Being hard to admonish and having bad friends."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.16"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.17"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What two things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.18"
msgid "Sovacassatā ca kalyāṇamittatā ca."
msgstr "Being easy to admonish and having good friends."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.19"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.20"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What two things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.21"
msgid ""
"Yo ca hetu yo ca paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya, yo ca hetu yo ca paccayo "
"sattānaṃ visuddhiyā."
msgstr ""
"What are the causes and conditions for the corruption of sentient beings, "
"and what are the causes and conditions for the purification of sentient "
"beings."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.22"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.23"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.24"
msgid "Dve ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Two knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.25"
msgid "khaye ñāṇaṃ, anuppāde ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "knowledge of ending, and knowledge of non-arising."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.26"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.27"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What two things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.28"
msgid "Dve dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Two elements:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.29"
msgid "saṅkhatā ca dhātu asaṅkhatā ca dhātu."
msgstr "the conditioned element and the unconditioned element."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.30"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.31"
msgid "Katame dve dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What two things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.32"
msgid "Vijjā ca vimutti ca."
msgstr "Knowledge and freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.3.33"
msgid "Ime dve dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.34"
msgid ""
"Iti ime vīsati dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these twenty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.3.35"
msgid "3. Tayo dhammā"
msgstr "3. Groups of Three"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.1"
msgid ""
"Tayo dhammā bahukārā, tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā … pe … tayo dhammā "
"sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Three things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.2"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What three things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.3"
msgid "Sappurisasaṃsevo, saddhammassavanaṃ, dhammānudhammappaṭipatti."
msgstr ""
"Associating with good people, listening to the true teaching, and practicing "
"in line with the teaching."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.4"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.5"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.6"
msgid "Tayo samādhī—"
msgstr "Three kinds of immersion."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.7"
msgid ""
"savitakko savicāro samādhi, avitakko vicāramatto samādhi, avitakko avicāro "
"samādhi."
msgstr ""
"Immersion with placing the mind and keeping it connected. Immersion without "
"placing the mind, but just keeping it connected. Immersion without placing "
"the mind or keeping it connected."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.8"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.275"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.9"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What three things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.10"
msgid "Tisso vedanā—"
msgstr "Three feelings:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.11"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.12"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.13"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.14"
msgid "Tisso taṇhā—"
msgstr "Three cravings:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.15"
msgid "kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā."
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving for continued existence, and craving "
"to end existence."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.16"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.17"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What three things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.18"
msgid "Tīṇi akusalamūlāni—"
msgstr "Three unskillful roots:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.19"
msgid "lobho akusalamūlaṃ, doso akusalamūlaṃ, moho akusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.20"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.21"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What three things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.22"
msgid "Tīṇi kusalamūlāni—"
msgstr "Three skillful roots:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.23"
msgid "alobho kusalamūlaṃ, adoso kusalamūlaṃ, amoho kusalamūlaṃ."
msgstr "non-greed, non-hate, and non-delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.24"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.25"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What three things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.26"
msgid "Tisso nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Three elements of escape."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.27"
msgid ""
"kāmānametaṃ nissaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ nekkhammaṃ, rūpānametaṃ nissaraṇaṃ yadidaṃ "
"arūpaṃ, yaṃ kho pana kiñci bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ, nirodho "
"tassa nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Renunciation is the escape from sensual pleasures. The formless is the "
"escape from form. Cessation is the escape from whatever is created, "
"conditioned, and dependently originated."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.28"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.29"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.30"
msgid "Tīṇi ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Three knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.31"
msgid "atītaṃse ñāṇaṃ, anāgataṃse ñāṇaṃ, paccuppannaṃse ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr "regarding the past, future, and present."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.32"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.33"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What three things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.34"
msgid "Tisso dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Three elements:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.35"
msgid "kāmadhātu, rūpadhātu, arūpadhātu."
msgstr "sensuality, form, and formlessness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.36"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.37"
msgid "Katame tayo dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What three things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.38"
msgid "Tisso vijjā—"
msgstr "Three knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.39"
msgid ""
"pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇaṃ vijjā, sattānaṃ cutūpapāte ñāṇaṃ vijjā, āsavānaṃ "
"khaye ñāṇaṃ vijjā."
msgstr ""
"recollection of past lives, knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient "
"beings, and knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn34:1.4.40"
msgid "Ime tayo dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.276"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.41"
msgid ""
"Iti ime tiṃsa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these thirty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.4.42"
msgid "4. Cattāro dhammā"
msgstr "4. Groups of Four"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.1"
msgid ""
"Cattāro dhammā bahukārā, cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā … pe … cattāro dhammā "
"sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Four things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What four things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.3"
msgid "Cattāri cakkāni—"
msgstr "Four situations:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.4"
msgid ""
"patirūpadesavāso, sappurisūpanissayo, attasammāpaṇidhi, pubbe ca katapuññatā."
msgstr ""
"living in a suitable region, relying on good people, right determination, "
"and past merit."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.5"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.7"
msgid "Cattāro satipaṭṭhānā—"
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.8"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and "
"mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.9"
msgid "Vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.10"
msgid "citte …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.11"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.12"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.13"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What four things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.14"
msgid "Cattāro āhārā—"
msgstr "Four foods:"

#. VAR: kabaḷīkāro → kavaḷīkāro (s1-3, km) | kabaliṅkāro (pts1)
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.15"
msgid ""
"kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, "
"viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention "
"the third, and consciousness the fourth."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.16"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.17"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.18"
msgid "Cattāro oghā—"
msgstr "Four floods:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.19"
msgid "kāmogho, bhavogho, diṭṭhogho, avijjogho."
msgstr "sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.20"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.21"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What four things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.22"
msgid "Cattāro yogā—"
msgstr "Four bonds:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.23"
msgid "kāmayogo, bhavayogo, diṭṭhiyogo, avijjāyogo."
msgstr "sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.24"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.25"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What four things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.26"
msgid "Cattāro visaṃyogā—"
msgstr "Four kinds of detachment:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.27"
msgid ""
"kāmayogavisaṃyogo, bhavayogavisaṃyogo, diṭṭhiyogavisaṃyogo, "
"avijjāyogavisaṃyogo."
msgstr ""
"detachment from the bonds of sensuality, desire for rebirth, views, and "
"ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.28"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.277"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.29"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What four things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.30"
msgid "Cattāro samādhī—"
msgstr "Four kinds of immersion:"

# In my view, this is almost certainly a mistake. Four sannas are more plausibly described in this way at AN 4.179. The sanskrit text at SF 107 has the four noble truths, which makes much more sense.
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.31"
msgid ""
"hānabhāgiyo samādhi, ṭhitibhāgiyo samādhi, visesabhāgiyo samādhi, "
"nibbedhabhāgiyo samādhi."
msgstr ""
"immersion liable to decline, stable immersion, immersion that leads to "
"distinction, and immersion that leads to penetration."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.32"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.33"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.34"
msgid "Cattāri ñāṇāni—"
msgstr "Four knowledges:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.35"
msgid "dhamme ñāṇaṃ, anvaye ñāṇaṃ, pariye ñāṇaṃ, sammutiyā ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"knowledge of the present phenomena, knowledge of what follows, knowledge of "
"others’ minds, and conventional knowledge."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.36"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.37"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What four things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.38"
msgid "Cattāri ariyasaccāni—"
msgstr "The four noble truths:"

#. VAR: dukkhanirodhaṃ → dukkhanirodho (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.39"
msgid ""
"dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ "
"ariyasaccaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ."
msgstr ""
"suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.40"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.41"
msgid "Katame cattāro dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What four things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.42"
msgid "Cattāri sāmaññaphalāni—"
msgstr "Four fruits of the ascetic life:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.43"
msgid "sotāpattiphalaṃ, sakadāgāmiphalaṃ, anāgāmiphalaṃ, arahattaphalaṃ."
msgstr "stream-entry, once-return, non-return, and perfection."

msgctxt "dn34:1.5.44"
msgid "Ime cattāro dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.45"
msgid ""
"Iti ime cattārīsadhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these forty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.5.46"
msgid "5. Pañca dhammā"
msgstr "5. Groups of Five"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.1"
msgid "Pañca dhammā bahukārā … pe … pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Five things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What five things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.3"
msgid "Pañca padhāniyaṅgāni—"
msgstr "Five factors that support meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.4"
msgid "idhāvuso, bhikkhu saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "A mendicant has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.5"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.6"
msgid ""
"Appābādho hoti appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya "
"nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya."
msgstr ""
"They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too "
"hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.7"
msgid ""
"Asaṭho hoti amāyāvī yathābhūtamattānaṃ āvīkattā satthari vā viññūsu vā "
"sabrahmacārīsu."
msgstr ""
"They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the "
"Teacher or sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.8"
msgid ""
"Āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and "
"gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking "
"off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.9"
msgid ""
"Paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is "
"noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.10"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.278"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.11"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.12"
msgid "Pañcaṅgiko sammāsamādhi—"
msgstr "Right immersion with five factors:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.13"
msgid ""
"pītipharaṇatā, sukhapharaṇatā, cetopharaṇatā, ālokapharaṇatā, "
"paccavekkhaṇanimittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"pervaded with rapture, pervaded with pleasure, pervaded with mind, pervaded "
"with light, and the basis for reviewing."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.14"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc54"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.15"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What five things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.16"
msgid "Pañcupādānakkhandhā—"
msgstr "Five grasping aggregates:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.17"
msgid ""
"rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr "form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.18"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc55"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.19"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.20"
msgid "Pañca nīvaraṇāni—"
msgstr "Five hindrances:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.21"
msgid ""
"kāmacchandanīvaraṇaṃ, byāpādanīvaraṇaṃ, thinamiddhanīvaraṇaṃ, "
"uddhaccakukkuccanīvaraṇaṃ, vicikicchānīvaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, "
"and doubt."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.22"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc56"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.23"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What five things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.24"
msgid "Pañca cetokhilā—"
msgstr "Five kinds of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.25"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant has doubts about the Teacher. They’re uncertain, "
"undecided, and lacking confidence."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.26"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu satthari kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na "
"sampasīdati, tassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, "
"persistence, and striving."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.27"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.28"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo cetokhilo."
msgstr "This is the first kind of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.29"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dhamme kaṅkhati vicikicchati … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has doubts about the teaching …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.30"
msgid "saṅghe kaṅkhati vicikicchati … pe …"
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.31"
msgid "sikkhāya kaṅkhati vicikicchati … pe …"
msgstr "the training …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.32"
msgid ""
"sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, yo so, āvuso, "
"bhikkhu sabrahmacārīsu kupito hoti anattamano āhatacitto khilajāto, tassa "
"cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant is angry and upset with their spiritual companions, resentful "
"and closed off."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.33"
msgid "Yassa cittaṃ na namati ātappāya anuyogāya sātaccāya padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"This being so, their mind doesn’t incline toward keenness, commitment, "
"persistence, and striving."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.34"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo cetokhilo."
msgstr "This is the fifth kind of emotional barrenness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.35"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc57"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.36"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What five things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.37"
msgid "Pañcindriyāni—"
msgstr "Five faculties:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.38"
msgid ""
"saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ."
msgstr "faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.39"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc58"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.40"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What five things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.41"
msgid "Pañca nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Five elements of escape."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.42"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāme manasikaroto kāmesu cittaṃ na pakkhandati na "
"pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant focuses on sensual pleasures, but their mind isn’t eager, "
"confident, settled, and decided about them."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.43"
msgid ""
"Nekkhammaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on renunciation, their mind is eager, confident, "
"settled, and decided about it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.44"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"kāmehi."
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.45"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kāmapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi. Na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of sensual pleasures, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.46"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ kāmānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (7.1)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from sensual pleasures is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc59"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.47"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno byāpādaṃ manasikaroto byāpāde cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on ill will, but their mind isn’"
"t eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.48"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto abyāpāde cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on love, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.49"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"byāpādena."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from ill will."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.50"
msgid ""
"Ye ca byāpādapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi. Na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of ill will, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.51"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ. (7.2)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from ill will is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc60"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.52"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno vihesaṃ manasikaroto vihesāya cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on harming, but their mind isn’t "
"eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.53"
msgid ""
"Avihesaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto avihesāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on compassion, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.54"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"vihesāya."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from harming."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.55"
msgid ""
"Ye ca vihesāpaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi. Na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of harming, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.56"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ vihesāya nissaraṇaṃ. (7.3)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from harming is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc61"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.57"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno rūpe manasikaroto rūpesu cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where a mendicant focuses on form, but their mind isn’t "
"eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.58"
msgid ""
"Arūpaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto arūpe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr "But when they focus on the formless, their mind is eager …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.59"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"rūpehi."
msgstr "Their mind is in a good state … well detached from forms."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.60"
msgid ""
"Ye ca rūpapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi. Na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of form, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.61"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. (7.4)"
msgstr "This is how the escape from forms is explained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc62"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.62"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno sakkāyaṃ manasikaroto sakkāye cittaṃ na "
"pakkhandati na pasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Take a case where a mendicant focuses on identity, but their mind isn’t "
"eager, confident, settled, and decided about it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.63"
msgid ""
"Sakkāyanirodhaṃ kho panassa manasikaroto sakkāyanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati "
"pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"But when they focus on the ending of identity, their mind is eager, "
"confident, settled, and decided about it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.64"
msgid ""
"Tassa taṃ cittaṃ sugataṃ subhāvitaṃ suvuṭṭhitaṃ suvimuttaṃ visaṃyuttaṃ "
"sakkāyena."
msgstr ""
"Their mind is in a good state, well developed, well risen, well freed, and "
"well detached from identity."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.65"
msgid ""
"Ye ca sakkāyapaccayā uppajjanti āsavā vighātā pariḷāhā, mutto so tehi. Na so "
"taṃ vedanaṃ vedeti."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from the distressing and feverish defilements that arise "
"because of identity, so they don’t experience that kind of feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.66"
msgid "Idamakkhātaṃ sakkāyassa nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is how the escape from identity is explained."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.67"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.279"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc63"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.68"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.69"
msgid "Pañca ñāṇiko sammāsamādhi:"
msgstr "Right immersion with five knowledges."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.70"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ samādhi paccuppannasukho ceva āyatiñca sukhavipāko’ti paccattaṃyeva "
"ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"The following knowledges arise for you personally: ‘This immersion is "
"blissful now, and results in bliss in the future.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.71"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ samādhi ariyo nirāmiso’ti paccattaññeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘This immersion is noble and spiritual.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.72"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ samādhi akāpurisasevito’ti paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘This immersion is not cultivated by sinners.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.73"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ samādhi santo paṇīto paṭippassaddhaladdho ekodibhāvādhigato, na "
"sasaṅkhāraniggayhavāritagato’ti paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"‘This immersion is peaceful and sublime and tranquil and unified, not held "
"in place by forceful suppression.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.74"
msgid ""
"‘So kho panāhaṃ imaṃ samādhiṃ satova samāpajjāmi sato vuṭṭhahāmī’ti "
"paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "‘I mindfully enter into and emerge from this immersion.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.75"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc64"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.76"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What five things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.77"
msgid "Pañca vimuttāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Five opportunities for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.78"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhuno satthā dhammaṃ deseti aññataro vā garuṭṭhāniyo "
"sabrahmacārī."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, the Teacher or a respected spiritual companion teaches Dhamma to a "
"mendicant."

#. VAR: tathā so → bhikkhu (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.79"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhuno satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro vā "
"garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca "
"hoti dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dhamma, no matter how the Teacher or a respected spiritual companion teaches "
"it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.80"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the "
"mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is "
"tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.81"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ. (9.1)"
msgstr "This is the first opportunity for freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc65"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.82"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti "
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor a respected spiritual "
"companion teaches Dhamma to a mendicant. But the mendicant teaches Dhamma in "
"detail to others as they learned and memorized it. "

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.83"
msgid ""
"yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena "
"paresaṃ deseti tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti "
"dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dhamma, no matter how they teach it in detail to others as they learned and "
"memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.84"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the "
"mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is "
"tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.85"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ. (9.2)"
msgstr "This is the second opportunity for freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc66"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.86"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti. Api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dhamma. But the mendicant recites the teaching in detail as they learned and "
"memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.87"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena "
"sajjhāyaṃ karoti tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti "
"dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dhamma, no matter how they recite it in detail as they learned and memorized "
"it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.88"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the "
"mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is "
"tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.89"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ. (9.3)"
msgstr "This is the third opportunity for freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc67"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.90"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dhamma … nor does the mendicant recite the teaching."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.91"
msgid ""
"Api ca kho yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakketi "
"anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati."
msgstr ""
"But the mendicant thinks about and considers the teaching in their heart, "
"examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.92"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā "
"anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati tathā tathā so tasmiṃ dhamme "
"atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammapaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dhamma, no matter how they think about and consider it in their heart, "
"examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.93"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammapaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the "
"mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is "
"tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.94"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ. (9.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth opportunity for freedom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc68"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.95"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno na heva kho satthā dhammaṃ deseti, aññataro "
"vā garuṭṭhāniyo sabrahmacārī, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena paresaṃ deseti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ "
"vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti, nāpi yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā "
"anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, it may be that neither the Teacher nor … the mendicant teaches "
"Dhamma … nor does the mendicant recite the teaching … or think about it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.96"
msgid ""
"api ca khvassa aññataraṃ samādhinimittaṃ suggahitaṃ hoti sumanasikataṃ "
"sūpadhāritaṃ suppaṭividdhaṃ paññāya."
msgstr ""
"But a meditation subject as a basis of immersion is properly grasped, "
"attended, borne in mind, and comprehended with wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.97"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā, āvuso, bhikkhuno aññataraṃ samādhinimittaṃ suggahitaṃ hoti "
"sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritaṃ suppaṭividdhaṃ paññāya tathā tathā so tasmiṃ "
"dhamme atthappaṭisaṃvedī ca hoti dhammappaṭisaṃvedī ca."
msgstr ""
"That mendicant feels inspired by the meaning and the teaching in that "
"Dhamma, no matter how a meditation subject as a basis of immersion is "
"properly grasped, attended, borne in mind, and comprehended with wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.98"
msgid ""
"Tassa atthappaṭisaṃvedino dhammappaṭisaṃvedino pāmojjaṃ jāyati, pamuditassa "
"pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, "
"sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Feeling inspired, joy springs up. Being joyful, rapture springs up. When the "
"mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is "
"tranquil, one feels bliss. And when blissful, the mind becomes immersed."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.99"
msgid "Idaṃ pañcamaṃ vimuttāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the fifth opportunity for freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.100"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc69"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.101"
msgid "Katame pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What five things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.102"
msgid "Pañca dhammakkhandhā—"
msgstr "Five spectrums of the teaching:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.103"
msgid ""
"sīlakkhandho, samādhikkhandho, paññākkhandho, vimuttikkhandho, "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.6.104"
msgid "Ime pañca dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc70"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.105"
msgid ""
"Iti ime paññāsa dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these fifty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.6.106"
msgid "6. Cha dhammā"
msgstr "6. Groups of Six"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc71"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.1"
msgid "Cha dhammā bahukārā … pe … cha dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Six things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.280"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc72"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.2"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What six things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.3"
msgid "Cha sāraṇīyā dhammā."
msgstr "Six warm-hearted qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.4"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti sabrahmacārīsu āvi "
"ceva raho ca, "
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"bodily kindness, both in public and in private. "

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.5"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1.1)"
msgstr ""
"This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to "
"inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc73"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.6"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ … pe … ekībhāvāya "
"saṃvattati. (1.2)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"verbal kindness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc74"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.7"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno mettaṃ manokammaṃ … pe … ekībhāvāya "
"saṃvattati. (1.3)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"mental kindness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc75"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.8"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso "
"pattapariyāpannamattampi, tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī hoti "
"sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo … pe … "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati. (1.4)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant shares without reservation any material possessions "
"they have gained by legitimate means, even the food placed in the alms-bowl, "
"using them in common with their ethical spiritual companions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc76"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.9"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu, yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni "
"asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni, tathārūpesu sīlesu sīlasāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo … pe … ekībhāvāya "
"saṃvattati. (1.5)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the precepts shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. Those precepts are "
"unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc77"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.10"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti takkarassa "
"sammā dukkhakkhayāya, tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhi sāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, "
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the view shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and "
"emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of "
"suffering. "

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.11"
msgid ""
"ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo piyakaraṇo garukaraṇo, saṅgahāya avivādāya sāmaggiyā "
"ekībhāvāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"This warm-hearted quality makes for fondness and respect, conducing to "
"inclusion, harmony, and unity, without quarreling."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.12"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā bahukārā. (1.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc78"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.13"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.14"
msgid "Cha anussatiṭṭhānāni—"
msgstr "Six recollections:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.15"
msgid ""
"buddhānussati, dhammānussati, saṅghānussati, sīlānussati, cāgānussati, "
"devatānussati."
msgstr ""
"the recollection of the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, ethics, "
"generosity, and the deities."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.16"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc79"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.17"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What six things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.18"
msgid "Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni—"
msgstr "Six interior sense fields:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.19"
msgid ""
"cakkhāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, "
"manāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.20"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc80"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.21"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.22"
msgid "Cha taṇhākāyā—"
msgstr "Six classes of craving:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.23"
msgid ""
"rūpataṇhā, saddataṇhā, gandhataṇhā, rasataṇhā, phoṭṭhabbataṇhā, dhammataṇhā."
msgstr "craving for sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.24"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc81"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.25"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What six things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.26"
msgid "Cha agāravā—"
msgstr "Six kinds of disrespect."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.27"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthari agāravo viharati appatisso. Dhamme … pe … saṅghe …"
" sikkhāya … appamāde … paṭisanthāre agāravo viharati appatisso."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant lacks respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, and "
"the Saṅgha, the training, diligence, and hospitality."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.28"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc82"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.29"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What six things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.30"
msgid "Cha gāravā—"
msgstr "Six kinds of respect."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.31"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthari sagāravo viharati sappatisso. Dhamme … pe … "
"saṅghe … sikkhāya … appamāde … paṭisanthāre sagāravo viharati sappatisso."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant has respect and reverence for the Teacher, the teaching, and the "
"Saṅgha, the training, diligence, and hospitality."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.32"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc83"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.33"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What six things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.34"
msgid "Cha nissaraṇiyā dhātuyo—"
msgstr "Six elements of escape."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.35"
msgid "idhāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take a mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.36"
msgid ""
"‘mettā hi kho me, cetovimutti bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā "
"anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, "
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve developed the heart’s release by love. I’ve cultivated it, made it my "
"vehicle and my basis, kept it up, consolidated it, and properly implemented "
"it. "

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.37"
msgid "atha ca pana me byāpādo cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow ill will still occupies my mind.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.38"
msgid ""
"So ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. "
"Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya."
msgstr ""
"They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! Don’t say that. Don’t misrepresent "
"the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha "
"would not say that."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.39"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhānametaṃ āvuso anavakāso yaṃ mettāya cetovimuttiyā bhāvitāya "
"bahulīkatāya yānīkatāya vatthukatāya anuṭṭhitāya paricitāya susamāraddhāya."
msgstr ""
"It’s impossible, reverend, it cannot happen that the heart’s release by love "
"has been developed and properly implemented,"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.40"
msgid ""
"Atha ca panassa byāpādo cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassatīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "yet somehow ill will still occupies the mind."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.41"
msgid "Nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, byāpādassa, yadidaṃ mettācetovimuttī’ti. (7.1)"
msgstr ""
"For it is the heart’s release by love that is the escape from ill will.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc84"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.42"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.43"
msgid ""
"‘karuṇā hi kho me cetovimutti bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā "
"anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve developed the heart’s release by compassion. I’ve cultivated it, made "
"it my vehicle and my basis, kept it up, consolidated it, and properly "
"implemented it."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.44"
msgid "Atha ca pana me vihesā cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow the thought of harming still occupies my mind.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.45"
msgid ""
"So: ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo, ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ "
"abbhācikkhi … pe …"
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.46"
msgid "nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, vihesāya, yadidaṃ karuṇācetovimuttī’ti. (7.2)"
msgstr ""
"For it is the heart’s release by compassion that is the escape from thoughts "
"of harming.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc85"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.47"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.48"
msgid "‘muditā hi kho me cetovimutti bhāvitā … pe …"
msgstr "‘I’ve developed the heart’s release by rejoicing. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.49"
msgid "atha ca pana me arati cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow negativity still occupies my mind.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.50"
msgid "So: ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca … pe …"
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.51"
msgid "nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, aratiyā, yadidaṃ muditācetovimuttī’ti. (7.3)"
msgstr ""
"For it is the heart’s release by rejoicing that is the escape from "
"negativity.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc86"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.52"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.53"
msgid "‘upekkhā hi kho me cetovimutti bhāvitā … pe …"
msgstr "‘I’ve developed the heart’s release by equanimity. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.54"
msgid "atha ca pana me rāgo cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow desire still occupies my mind.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.55"
msgid "So: ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca … pe …"
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.56"
msgid "nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, rāgassa yadidaṃ upekkhācetovimuttī’ti. (7.4)"
msgstr ""
"For it is the heart’s release by equanimity that is the escape from desire.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc87"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.57"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.58"
msgid "‘animittā hi kho me cetovimutti bhāvitā … pe …"
msgstr "‘I’ve developed the signless heart’s release. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.59"
msgid "atha ca pana me nimittānusāri viññāṇaṃ hotī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow my consciousness still follows after signs.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.60"
msgid "So: ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca … pe …"
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.61"
msgid ""
"nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, sabbanimittānaṃ yadidaṃ animittā cetovimuttī’ti. "
"(7.5)"
msgstr ""
"For it is the signless release of the heart that is the escape from all "
"signs.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc88"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.62"
msgid "Idha panāvuso, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.63"
msgid "‘asmīti kho me vigataṃ, ayamahamasmīti na samanupassāmi, "
msgstr ""
"‘I’m rid of the conceit “I am”. And I don’t regard anything as “I am this”. "

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.64"
msgid ""
"atha ca pana me vicikicchākathaṅkathāsallaṃ cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī’ti."
msgstr "Yet somehow the dart of doubt and indecision still occupies my mind.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.65"
msgid ""
"So: ‘mā hevan’tissa vacanīyo ‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ "
"abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya."
msgstr ""
"They should be told, ‘Not so, venerable! Don’t say that. Don’t misrepresent "
"the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha "
"would not say that."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.66"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhānametaṃ, āvuso, anavakāso yaṃ asmīti vigate ayamahamasmīti "
"asamanupassato."
msgstr ""
"It’s impossible, reverend, it cannot happen that the conceit “I am” has been "
"done away with, and nothing is regarded as “I am this”,"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.67"
msgid ""
"Atha ca panassa vicikicchākathaṅkathāsallaṃ cittaṃ pariyādāya ṭhassati, "
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "yet somehow the dart of doubt and indecision still occupy the mind."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.68"
msgid ""
"Nissaraṇaṃ hetaṃ, āvuso, vicikicchākathaṅkathāsallassa, yadidaṃ "
"asmimānasamugghāto’ti."
msgstr ""
"For it is the uprooting of the conceit “I am” that is the escape from the "
"dart of doubt and indecision.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.69"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.281"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc89"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.70"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.71"
msgid "Cha satatavihārā."
msgstr "Six consistent responses."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.72"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano, "
"upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant, seeing a sight with their eyes, is neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.73"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "Hearing a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.74"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "Smelling an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.75"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.76"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "Feeling a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.77"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato "
"sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"Knowing a thought with their mind, they’re neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.78"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc90"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.79"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What six things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.80"
msgid "Cha anuttariyāni—"
msgstr "Six unsurpassable things:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.81"
msgid ""
"dassanānuttariyaṃ, savanānuttariyaṃ, lābhānuttariyaṃ, sikkhānuttariyaṃ, "
"pāricariyānuttariyaṃ, anussatānuttariyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"the unsurpassable seeing, listening, acquisition, training, service, and "
"recollection."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.82"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc91"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.83"
msgid "Katame cha dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What six things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.84"
msgid "Cha abhiññā—"
msgstr "Six direct knowledges."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.85"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—ekopi hutvā bahudhā "
"hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ "
"tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi "
"ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati "
"seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; "
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti. (10.1)"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying themselves "
"and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through "
"a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of "
"the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying "
"cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with the "
"hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling the body as far "
"as the Brahmā realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc92"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.86"
msgid ""
"Dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇāti dibbe "
"ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike ca. (10.2)"
msgstr ""
"With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, they hear both kinds of "
"sounds, human and divine, whether near or far."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc93"></a>
#. VAR: pajānāti → jānāti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.87"
msgid ""
"Parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti, sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ "
"sarāgaṃ cittanti pajānāti … pe … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti "
"pajānāti. (10.3)"
msgstr ""
"They understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having "
"comprehended them with their own mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc94"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.88"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti "
"sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati. (10.4)"
msgstr "They recollect many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc95"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.89"
msgid ""
"Dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāti … pe … (10.5)"
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings are reborn "
"according to their deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc96"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.90"
msgid ""
"Āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "dn34:1.7.91"
msgid "Ime cha dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc97"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.92"
msgid ""
"Iti ime saṭṭhi dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these sixty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.7.93"
msgid "7. Satta dhammā"
msgstr "7. Groups of Seven"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs1.8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.282"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc98"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.1"
msgid "Satta dhammā bahukārā … pe … satta dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Seven things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc99"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.2"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What seven things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.3"
msgid "Satta ariyadhanāni—"
msgstr "Seven kinds of noble wealth:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.4"
msgid ""
"saddhādhanaṃ, sīladhanaṃ, hiridhanaṃ, ottappadhanaṃ, sutadhanaṃ, cāgadhanaṃ, "
"paññādhanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"the wealth of faith, ethical conduct, conscience, prudence, learning, "
"generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.5"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc100"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.6"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.7"
msgid "Satta sambojjhaṅgā—"
msgstr "Seven awakening factors:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.8"
msgid ""
"satisambojjhaṅgo, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo, "
"pītisambojjhaṅgo, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo, samādhisambojjhaṅgo, "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, "
"immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.9"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc101"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.10"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.11"
msgid "Satta viññāṇaṭṭhitiyo—"
msgstr "Seven planes of consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.12"
msgid ""
"santāvuso, sattā nānattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca "
"devā ekacce ca vinipātikā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as human beings, some gods, and some beings in the "
"underworld."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamā viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.1)"
msgstr "This is the first plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc102"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.14"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā nānattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā brahmakāyikā "
"paṭhamābhinibbattā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods reborn in Brahmā’s Group through the first "
"absorption."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyā viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.2)"
msgstr "This is the second plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc103"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.16"
msgid "Santāvuso, sattā ekattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā ābhassarā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as the gods of streaming radiance."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.17"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyā viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.3)"
msgstr "This is the third plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc104"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.18"
msgid "Santāvuso, sattā ekattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods replete with glory."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.19"
msgid "Ayaṃ catutthī viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc105"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.20"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā … pe … ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond perceptions of form. "
"With the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they have been reborn in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamī viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc106"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.22"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite space. Aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.23"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭhī viññāṇaṭṭhiti. (3.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth plane of consciousness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc107"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.24"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti "
"ākiñcaññāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness. Aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.25"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamī viññāṇaṭṭhiti."
msgstr "This is the seventh plane of consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.26"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā pariññeyyā. (3.7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc108"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.27"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.28"
msgid "Sattānusayā—"
msgstr "Seven underlying tendencies:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.29"
msgid ""
"kāmarāgānusayo, paṭighānusayo, diṭṭhānusayo, vicikicchānusayo, mānānusayo, "
"bhavarāgānusayo, avijjānusayo."
msgstr ""
"sensual desire, repulsion, views, doubt, conceit, desire to be reborn, and "
"ignorance."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.30"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc109"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.31"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What seven things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.32"
msgid "Satta asaddhammā—"
msgstr "Seven bad qualities:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.33"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu assaddho hoti, ahiriko hoti, anottappī hoti, appassuto "
"hoti, kusīto hoti, muṭṭhassati hoti, duppañño hoti."
msgstr ""
"a mendicant is faithless, shameless, imprudent, uneducated, lazy, unmindful, "
"and witless."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.34"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc110"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.35"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What seven things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.36"
msgid "Satta saddhammā—"
msgstr "Seven good qualities:"

#. VAR: hirimā → hiriko (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.37"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu saddho hoti, hirimā hoti, ottappī hoti, bahussuto hoti, "
"āraddhavīriyo hoti, upaṭṭhitassati hoti, paññavā hoti."
msgstr ""
"a mendicant is faithful, conscientious, prudent, learned, energetic, "
"mindful, and wise."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.38"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.283"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc111"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.39"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What seven things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.40"
msgid "Satta sappurisadhammā—"
msgstr "Seven aspects of the teachings of the good persons:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.41"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu dhammaññū ca hoti atthaññū ca attaññū ca mattaññū ca "
"kālaññū ca parisaññū ca puggalaññū ca."
msgstr ""
"a mendicant knows the teachings, knows the meaning, knows themselves, knows "
"moderation, knows the right time, knows assemblies, and knows people."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.42"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc112"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.43"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.44"
msgid "Satta saññā—"
msgstr "Seven perceptions:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.45"
msgid ""
"aniccasaññā, anattasaññā, asubhasaññā, ādīnavasaññā, pahānasaññā, "
"virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā."
msgstr ""
"the perception of impermanence, the perception of not-self, the perception "
"of ugliness, the perception of drawbacks, the perception of giving up, the "
"perception of fading away, and the perception of cessation."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.46"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc113"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.47"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.48"
msgid "Satta niddasavatthūni—"
msgstr "Seven qualifications for graduation."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.49"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu sikkhāsamādāne tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca sikkhāsamādāne "
"avigatapemo."
msgstr "A mendicant has a keen enthusiasm to undertake the training …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.50"
msgid ""
"Dhammanisantiyā tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca dhammanisantiyā avigatapemo."
msgstr "to examine the teachings …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.51"
msgid "Icchāvinaye tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca icchāvinaye avigatapemo."
msgstr "to get rid of desires …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.52"
msgid "Paṭisallāne tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca paṭisallāne avigatapemo."
msgstr "for retreat …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.53"
msgid "Vīriyārambhe tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca vīriyārambhe avigatapemo."
msgstr "to rouse up energy …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.54"
msgid "Satinepakke tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca satinepakke avigatapemo."
msgstr "for mindfulness and alertness …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.55"
msgid ""
"Diṭṭhipaṭivedhe tibbacchando hoti, āyatiñca diṭṭhipaṭivedhe avigatapemo."
msgstr ""
"to comprehend theoretically. And they don’t lose these desires in the future."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.56"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc114"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.57"
msgid "Katame satta dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What seven things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.58"
msgid "Satta khīṇāsavabalāni—"
msgstr "Seven powers of one who has ended the defilements."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.59"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aniccato sabbe saṅkhārā yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant with defilements ended has clearly seen with right "
"wisdom all conditions as truly impermanent."

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.60"
msgid ""
"Yaṃpāvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aniccato sabbe saṅkhārā yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti, idampi khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ "
"balaṃ āgamma khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti: ‘khīṇā me āsavā’"
"ti. (10.1)"
msgstr ""
"This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to "
"claim: ‘My defilements have ended.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc115"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.61"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhā honti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has clearly seen with right "
"wisdom that sensual pleasures are truly like a pit of glowing coals. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.62"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso … pe … ‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (10.2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc116"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.63"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno vivekaninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti "
"vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāraṃ vivekaṭṭhaṃ nekkhammābhirataṃ byantībhūtaṃ "
"sabbaso āsavaṭṭhāniyehi dhammehi."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the mind of a mendicant with defilements ended slants, slopes, "
"and inclines to seclusion. They’re withdrawn, loving renunciation, and they’"
"ve totally done with defiling influences. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.64"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso … pe … ‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (10.3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.284"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc117"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.65"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā "
"honti subhāvitā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the four "
"kinds of mindfulness meditation. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.66"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso … pe … ‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (10.4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc118"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.67"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pañcindriyāni bhāvitāni honti "
"subhāvitāni."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the five "
"faculties. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.68"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso … pe … ‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (10.5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc119"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.69"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno satta bojjhaṅgā bhāvitā honti "
"subhāvitā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the seven "
"awakening factors. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.70"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso … pe … ‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti. (10.6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc120"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.71"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvito "
"hoti subhāvito."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant with defilements ended has well developed the noble "
"eightfold path. …"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.72"
msgid ""
"Yaṃpāvuso, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvito hoti "
"subhāvito, idampi khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno balaṃ hoti, yaṃ balaṃ āgamma "
"khīṇāsavo bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ paṭijānāti:"
msgstr ""
"This is a power that a mendicant who has ended the defilements relies on to "
"claim:"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.73"
msgid "‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti."
msgstr "‘My defilements have ended.’"

msgctxt "dn34:1.8.74"
msgid "Ime satta dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10.7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc121"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.75"
msgid ""
"Itime sattati dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these seventy things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.76"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The first recitation section is finished."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:1.8.77"
msgid "8. Aṭṭha dhammā"
msgstr "8. Groups of Eight"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2.1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc122"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.1"
msgid "Aṭṭha dhammā bahukārā … pe … aṭṭha dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Eight things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.285"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc123"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What eight things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.3"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭha hetū aṭṭha paccayā ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"There are eight causes and reasons that lead to acquiring the wisdom "
"fundamental to the spiritual life, and to its increase, growth, development, "
"and fulfillment once it has been acquired."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.4"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

#. VAR: satthāraṃ → satthāraṃ vā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.5"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu satthāraṃ upanissāya viharati aññataraṃ vā garuṭṭhāniyaṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ, yatthassa tibbaṃ hirottappaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti pemañca "
"gāravo ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant lives relying on the Teacher or a spiritual companion "
"in a teacher’s role. And they set up a keen sense of conscience and prudence "
"for them, with warmth and respect."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ paṭhamo hetu paṭhamo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.1)"
msgstr "This is the first cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc124"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.7"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana satthāraṃ upanissāya viharati aññataraṃ vā garuṭṭhāniyaṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ, yatthassa tibbaṃ hirottappaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti pemañca "
"gāravo ca. Te kālena kālaṃ upasaṅkamitvā paripucchati paripañhati:"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant lives relying on the Teacher or a spiritual companion in a "
"teacher’s role—with a keen sense of conscience and prudence for them, with "
"warmth and respect—from time to time they go and ask them questions:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.8"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ?"
msgstr "‘Why, sir, does it say this?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.9"
msgid "Imassa ko attho’ti?"
msgstr "What does that mean?’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa te āyasmanto avivaṭañceva vivaranti, anuttānīkatañca uttānīkaronti, "
"anekavihitesu ca kaṅkhāṭṭhāniyesu dhammesu kaṅkhaṃ paṭivinodenti."
msgstr ""
"Those venerables clarify what is unclear, reveal what is obscure, and dispel "
"doubt regarding the many doubtful matters."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ dutiyo hetu dutiyo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya, vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.2)"
msgstr "This is the second cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc125"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.12"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana dhammaṃ sutvā dvayena vūpakāsena sampādeti—kāyavūpakāsena ca "
"cittavūpakāsena ca."
msgstr ""
"After hearing that teaching they perfect withdrawal of both body and mind."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.13"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ tatiyo hetu tatiyo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.3)"
msgstr "This is the third cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc126"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.14"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno, aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"has appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.15"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ catuttho hetu catuttho paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya "
"appaṭiladdhāya paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya "
"pāripūriyā saṃvattati. (1.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc127"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.16"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te "
"dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthā sabyañjanā "
"kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā "
"bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā "
"suppaṭividdhā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is very learned, remembering and keeping what they’"
"ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, "
"and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual "
"practice that’s entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such "
"teachings, remembering them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally "
"scrutinizing them, and comprehending them theoretically."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.17"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ pañcamo hetu pañcamo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.286"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc128"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.18"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up "
"unskillful qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They are strong, "
"staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful "
"qualities."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.19"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ chaṭṭho hetu chaṭṭho paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc129"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.20"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu satimā hoti paramena satinepakkena samannāgato. "
"Cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and "
"alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.21"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ sattamo hetu sattamo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati. (1.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh cause."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc130"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.22"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu, udayabbayānupassī "
"viharati:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five "
"grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.23"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ iti rūpassa samudayo iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.24"
msgid "iti vedanā iti vedanāya samudayo iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of "
"feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.25"
msgid "iti saññā iti saññāya samudayo iti saññāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of "
"perception."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.26"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of "
"choices."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.27"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ iti viññāṇassa samudayo iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti."
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.28"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo hetu aṭṭhamo paccayo ādibrahmacariyikāya paññāya appaṭiladdhāya "
"paṭilābhāya, paṭiladdhāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr "This is the eighth cause."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.29"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā bahukārā. (1.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc131"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.30"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.31"
msgid "Ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "The noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.32"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, "
"sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.33"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc132"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.34"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.35"
msgid "Aṭṭha lokadhammā—"
msgstr "Eight worldly conditions:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.36"
msgid ""
"lābho ca, alābho ca, yaso ca, ayaso ca, nindā ca, pasaṃsā ca, sukhañca, "
"dukkhañca."
msgstr "gain and loss, fame and disgrace, praise and blame, pleasure and pain."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.37"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.287"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc133"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.38"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.39"
msgid "Aṭṭha micchattā—"
msgstr "Eight wrong ways:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.40"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, "
"micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, "
"wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.41"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc134"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.42"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What eight things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.43"
msgid "Aṭṭha kusītavatthūni."
msgstr "Eight grounds for laziness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.44"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhunā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant has some work to do. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.45"
msgid "tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.46"
msgid ""
"‘kammaṃ kho me kātabbaṃ bhavissati, kammaṃ kho pana me karontassa kāyo "
"kilamissati, handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I have some work to do. But while doing it my body will get tired. I’d "
"better have a lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.47"
msgid ""
"So nipajjati, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa "
"adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"They lie down, and don’t rouse energy for attaining the unattained, "
"achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.48"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.1)"
msgstr "This is the first ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc135"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.49"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā kammaṃ kataṃ hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has done some work."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.50"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.51"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho kammaṃ akāsiṃ, kammaṃ kho pana me karontassa kāyo kilanto, "
"handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve done some work. But while working my body got tired. I’d better have a "
"lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.52"
msgid "So nipajjati, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.53"
msgid "idaṃ dutiyaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.2)"
msgstr "This is the second ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc136"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.54"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā maggo gantabbo hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has to go on a journey."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.55"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.56"
msgid ""
"‘maggo kho me gantabbo bhavissati, maggaṃ kho pana me gacchantassa kāyo "
"kilamissati, handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I have to go on a journey. But while walking my body will get tired. I’d "
"better have a lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.57"
msgid "So nipajjati, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.58"
msgid "idaṃ tatiyaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.3)"
msgstr "This is the third ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc137"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.59"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā maggo gato hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has gone on a journey."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.60"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.61"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho maggaṃ agamāsiṃ, maggaṃ kho pana me gacchantassa kāyo kilanto, "
"handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve gone on a journey. But while walking my body got tired. I’d better "
"have a lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.62"
msgid "So nipajjati, na vīriyaṃ ārabhati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.63"
msgid "idaṃ catutthaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc138"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.64"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto na labhati "
"lūkhassa vā paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant has wandered for alms, but they didn’t get to fill "
"up on as much food as they like, coarse or fine."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.65"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.66"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto nālatthaṃ lūkhassa vā "
"paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ, tassa me kāyo kilanto "
"akammañño, handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve wandered for alms, but I didn’t get to fill up on as much food as I "
"like, coarse or fine. My body is tired and unfit for work. I’d better have a "
"lie down.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.67"
msgid "idaṃ pañcamaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc139"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.68"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto labhati "
"lūkhassa vā paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant has wandered for alms, and they got to fill up on "
"as much food as they like, coarse or fine."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.69"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.70"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto alatthaṃ lūkhassa vā paṇītassa "
"vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ, tassa me kāyo garuko akammañño, "
"māsācitaṃ maññe, handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve wandered for alms, and I got to fill up on as much food as I like, "
"coarse or fine. My body is heavy, unfit for work, like I’ve just eaten a "
"load of beans. I’d better have a lie down.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.71"
msgid "So nipajjati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.72"
msgid "idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc140"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.73"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno uppanno hoti appamattako ābādho, tassa evaṃ "
"hoti:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant feels a little sick. They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.74"
msgid ""
"‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ appamattako ābādho atthi kappo nipajjituṃ, handāhaṃ "
"nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I feel a little sick. Lying down would be good for me. I’d better have a "
"lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.75"
msgid "So nipajjati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.76"
msgid "idaṃ sattamaṃ kusītavatthu. (5.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh ground for laziness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc141"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.77"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gilānāvuṭṭhito hoti aciravuṭṭhito gelaññā."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has recently recovered from illness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.78"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.79"
msgid "‘ahaṃ kho gilānāvuṭṭhito aciravuṭṭhito gelaññā."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve recently recovered from illness. My body is weak and unfit for work. I’"
"d better have a lie down.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.80"
msgid "Tassa me kāyo dubbalo akammañño, handāhaṃ nipajjāmī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.81"
msgid "So nipajjati … pe …"
msgstr "They lie down, and don’t rouse energy ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.82"
msgid "idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ kusītavatthu."
msgstr "This is the eighth ground for laziness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.83"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc142"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.84"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What eight things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.85"
msgid "Aṭṭha ārambhavatthūni."
msgstr "Eight grounds for arousing energy."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.86"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhunā kammaṃ kātabbaṃ hoti, tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant has some work to do. They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.87"
msgid ""
"‘kammaṃ kho me kātabbaṃ bhavissati, kammaṃ kho pana me karontena na sukaraṃ "
"buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasikātuṃ, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā "
"anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I have some work to do. While working it’s not easy to focus on the "
"instructions of the Buddhas. I’d better preemptively rouse up energy for "
"attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, and realizing the "
"unrealized.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.88"
msgid ""
"So vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya "
"asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"They rouse energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, "
"and realizing the unrealized."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.89"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.1)"
msgstr "This is the first ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc143"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.90"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā kammaṃ kataṃ hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has done some work."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.91"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.92"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho kammaṃ akāsiṃ, kammaṃ kho panāhaṃ karonto nāsakkhiṃ buddhānaṃ "
"sāsanaṃ manasikātuṃ, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve done some work. While I was working I wasn’t able to focus on the "
"instructions of the Buddhas. I’d better preemptively rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.93"
msgid "idaṃ dutiyaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.2)"
msgstr "This is the second ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc144"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.94"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā maggo gantabbo hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has to go on a journey."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.95"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.96"
msgid ""
"‘maggo kho me gantabbo bhavissati, maggaṃ kho pana me gacchantena na sukaraṃ "
"buddhānaṃ sāsanaṃ manasikātuṃ, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I have to go on a journey. While walking it’s not easy to focus on the "
"instructions of the Buddhas. I’d better preemptively rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.97"
msgid "idaṃ tatiyaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.3)"
msgstr "This is the third ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc145"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.98"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhunā maggo gato hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has gone on a journey."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.99"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.100"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho maggaṃ agamāsiṃ, maggaṃ kho panāhaṃ gacchanto nāsakkhiṃ buddhānaṃ "
"sāsanaṃ manasikātuṃ, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve gone on a journey. While I was walking I wasn’t able to focus on the "
"instructions of the Buddhas. I’d better preemptively rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.101"
msgid "idaṃ catutthaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc146"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.102"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto na labhati "
"lūkhassa vā paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant has wandered for alms, but they didn’t get to fill "
"up on as much food as they like, coarse or fine."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.103"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.104"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto nālatthaṃ lūkhassa vā "
"paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ, tassa me kāyo lahuko "
"kammañño, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve wandered for alms, but I didn’t get to fill up on as much food as I "
"like, coarse or fine. My body is light and fit for work. I’d better "
"preemptively rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.105"
msgid "idaṃ pañcamaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc147"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.106"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto labhati "
"lūkhassa vā paṇītassa vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant has wandered for alms, and they got to fill up on "
"as much food as they like, coarse or fine."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.107"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.108"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya caranto alatthaṃ lūkhassa vā paṇītassa "
"vā bhojanassa yāvadatthaṃ pāripūriṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve wandered for alms, and I got to fill up on as much food as I like, "
"coarse or fine. My body is strong and fit for work. I’d better preemptively "
"rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.109"
msgid "Tassa me kāyo balavā kammañño, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.110"
msgid "idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc148"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.111"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhuno uppanno hoti appamattako ābādho."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant feels a little sick."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.112"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.113"
msgid ""
"‘uppanno kho me ayaṃ appamattako ābādho ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, yaṃ me "
"ābādho pavaḍḍheyya, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"‘I feel a little sick. It’s possible this illness will worsen. I’d better "
"preemptively rouse up energy.’ ..."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.114"
msgid "idaṃ sattamaṃ ārambhavatthu. (6.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh ground for arousing energy."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc149"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.115"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu gilānā vuṭṭhito hoti aciravuṭṭhito gelaññā."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has recently recovered from illness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.116"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.117"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho gilānā vuṭṭhito aciravuṭṭhito gelaññā, ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati, "
"yaṃ me ābādho paccudāvatteyya, handāhaṃ vīriyaṃ ārabhāmi appattassa pattiyā "
"anadhigatassa adhigamāya asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve recently recovered from illness. It’s possible the illness will come "
"back. I’d better preemptively rouse up energy for attaining the unattained, "
"achieving the unachieved, and realizing the unrealized.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.118"
msgid ""
"So vīriyaṃ ārabhati appattassa pattiyā anadhigatassa adhigamāya "
"asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāya."
msgstr ""
"They rouse energy for attaining the unattained, achieving the unachieved, "
"and realizing the unrealized."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.119"
msgid "Idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ ārambhavatthu."
msgstr "This is the eighth ground for arousing energy."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.120"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc150"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.121"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What eight things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.122"
msgid "Aṭṭha akkhaṇā asamayā brahmacariyavāsāya."
msgstr "Eight lost opportunities for spiritual practice."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.123"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, tathāgato ca loke uppanno hoti arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca "
"desiyati opasamiko parinibbāniko sambodhagāmī sugatappavedito."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a Realized One has arisen in the world. He teaches the Dhamma "
"leading to peace, extinguishment, awakening, as proclaimed by the Holy One."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.124"
msgid "Ayañca puggalo nirayaṃ upapanno hoti."
msgstr "But a person has been reborn in hell."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.125"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.1)"
msgstr "This is the first lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc151"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.126"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, tathāgato ca loke uppanno hoti arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, "
"dhammo ca desiyati opasamiko parinibbāniko sambodhagāmī sugatappavedito."
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.127"
msgid "Ayañca puggalo tiracchānayoniṃ upapanno hoti."
msgstr "But a person has been reborn in the animal realm."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.128"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.2)"
msgstr "This is the second lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc152"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.129"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.130"
msgid "pettivisayaṃ upapanno hoti."
msgstr "But a person has been reborn in the ghost realm."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.131"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.3)"
msgstr "This is the third lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc153"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.132"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.133"
msgid "aññataraṃ dīghāyukaṃ devanikāyaṃ upapanno hoti."
msgstr "But person has been reborn in one of the long-lived orders of gods."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.134"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc154"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.135"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.136"
msgid ""
"paccantimesu janapadesu paccājāto hoti milakkhesu aviññātāresu, yattha "
"natthi gati bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But a person has been reborn in the borderlands, among barbarian tribes, "
"where monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen do not go."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.137"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc155"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.138"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.139"
msgid ""
"ayañca puggalo majjhimesu janapadesu paccājāto hoti, so ca hoti "
"micchādiṭṭhiko viparītadassano:"
msgstr ""
"And a person is reborn in a central country. But they have wrong view and "
"distorted perspective:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.140"
msgid ""
"‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ "
"kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko, natthi mātā, "
"natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā "
"sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedentī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or "
"result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There are no duties to "
"mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no "
"ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the "
"afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.141"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭho akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc156"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.142"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.143"
msgid ""
"ayañca puggalo majjhimesu janapadesu paccājāto hoti, so ca hoti duppañño "
"jaḷo eḷamūgo, nappaṭibalo subhāsitadubbhāsitānamatthamaññātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And a person is reborn in a central country. But they’re witless, dull, "
"stupid, and unable to distinguish the well said from the poorly said."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.144"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya. (7.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc157"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.145"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a Realized One has arisen in the world."

# That this is the correct sense is inferred from DN 33 and AN 8.29.
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.146"
msgid ""
"ayañca puggalo majjhimesu janapadesu paccājāto hoti, so ca hoti paññavā "
"ajaḷo aneḷamūgo, paṭibalo subhāsitadubbhāsitānamatthamaññātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"But he doesn’t teach the Dhamma leading to peace, extinguishment, awakening, "
"as announced by the Holy One. And a person is reborn in a central country. "
"And they’re wise, bright, clever, and able to distinguish the well said from "
"the poorly said."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.147"
msgid "Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo akkhaṇo asamayo brahmacariyavāsāya."
msgstr "This is the eighth lost opportunity for spiritual practice."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.148"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc158"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.149"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.150"
msgid "Aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakkā—"
msgstr "Eight thoughts of a great man."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.151"
msgid "appicchassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassa."
msgstr "‘This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.152"
msgid "Santuṭṭhassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassa."
msgstr "It’s for the contented, not the discontented."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.153"
msgid "Pavivittassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassa."
msgstr "It’s for the secluded, not those who enjoy company."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.154"
msgid "Āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassa."
msgstr "It’s for the energetic, not the lazy."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.155"
msgid "Upaṭṭhitasatissāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo muṭṭhassatissa."
msgstr "It’s for the mindful, not the unmindful."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.156"
msgid "Samāhitassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassa."
msgstr "It’s for those with immersion, not those without immersion."

#. VAR: Paññavato → paññāvato (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.157"
msgid "Paññavato ayaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassa."
msgstr "It’s for the wise, not the witless."

# Following BJT reading.
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.158"
msgid ""
"Nippapañcassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo papañcārāmassāti ime aṭṭha dhammā "
"uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""
"This teaching is for those who don’t enjoy proliferating, not for those who "
"enjoy proliferating.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc159"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.159"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.160"
msgid "Aṭṭha abhibhāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Eight dimensions of mastery."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.161"
msgid ""
"ajjhattaṃ rūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati parittāni suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni, "
"‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limited, both "
"pretty and ugly. Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.162"
msgid "evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.163"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.1)"
msgstr "This is the first dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc160"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.164"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ rūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati appamāṇāni "
"suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limitless, both "
"pretty and ugly. Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.165"
msgid "evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.166"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.2)"
msgstr "This is the second dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc161"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.167"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati parittāni "
"suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limited, "
"both pretty and ugly. Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.168"
msgid "evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.169"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.3)"
msgstr "This is the third dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc162"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.170"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati appamāṇāni "
"suvaṇṇadubbaṇṇāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally, limitless, "
"both pretty and ugly. Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.171"
msgid "evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.172"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc163"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.173"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati nīlāni nīlavaṇṇāni "
"nīlanidassanāni nīlanibhāsāni."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are "
"blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.174"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma umāpupphaṃ nīlaṃ nīlavaṇṇaṃ nīlanidassanaṃ nīlanibhāsaṃ, "
"seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ nīlaṃ "
"nīlavaṇṇaṃ nīlanidassanaṃ nīlanibhāsaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like a flax flower that’s blue, with blue color, blue hue, and blue "
"tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, blue, with "
"blue color, blue hue, and blue tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.175"
msgid ""
"evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati nīlāni nīlavaṇṇāni "
"nīlanidassanāni nīlanibhāsāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti evaṃsaññī "
"hoti."
msgstr "Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.176"
msgid "Idaṃ pañcamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc164"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.177"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati pītāni pītavaṇṇāni "
"pītanidassanāni pītanibhāsāni."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are "
"yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.178"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma kaṇikārapupphaṃ pītaṃ pītavaṇṇaṃ pītanidassanaṃ "
"pītanibhāsaṃ, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ "
"ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ pītaṃ pītavaṇṇaṃ pītanidassanaṃ pītanibhāsaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like a champak flower that’s yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, "
"and yellow tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, "
"yellow, with yellow color, yellow hue, and yellow tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.179"
msgid ""
"evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati pītāni pītavaṇṇāni "
"pītanidassanāni pītanibhāsāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi passāmī’ti evaṃsaññī "
"hoti."
msgstr "Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.180"
msgid "Idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc165"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.181"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati lohitakāni lohitakavaṇṇāni "
"lohitakanidassanāni lohitakanibhāsāni."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are "
"red, with red color, red hue, and red tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.182"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma bandhujīvakapupphaṃ lohitakaṃ lohitakavaṇṇaṃ "
"lohitakanidassanaṃ lohitakanibhāsaṃ, seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ "
"bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ lohitakaṃ lohitakavaṇṇaṃ "
"lohitakanidassanaṃ lohitakanibhāsaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like a scarlet mallow flower that’s red, with red color, red hue, "
"and red tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, red, "
"with red color, red hue, and red tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.183"
msgid ""
"evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati lohitakāni "
"lohitakavaṇṇāni lohitakanidassanāni lohitakanibhāsāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya "
"jānāmi passāmī’ti evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr "Mastering them, they perceive: ‘I know and see.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.184"
msgid "Idaṃ sattamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ. (9.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh dimension of mastery."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc166"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.185"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati odātāni odātavaṇṇāni "
"odātanidassanāni odātanibhāsāni."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, someone sees visions externally that are "
"white, with white color, white hue, and white tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.186"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma osadhitārakā odātā odātavaṇṇā odātanidassanā odātanibhāsā, "
"seyyathā vā pana taṃ vatthaṃ bārāṇaseyyakaṃ ubhatobhāgavimaṭṭhaṃ odātaṃ "
"odātavaṇṇaṃ odātanidassanaṃ odātanibhāsaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They’re like the morning star that’s white, with white color, white hue, and "
"white tint. Or a cloth from Bāraṇasī that’s smoothed on both sides, white, "
"with white color, white hue, and white tint."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.187"
msgid ""
"evameva ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati odātāni "
"odātavaṇṇāni odātanidassanāni odātanibhāsāni, ‘tāni abhibhuyya jānāmi "
"passāmī’ti evaṃsaññī hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.188"
msgid "Idaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ abhibhāyatanaṃ."
msgstr "This is the eighth dimension of mastery."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.189"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.288"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc167"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.190"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What eight things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.191"
msgid "Aṭṭha vimokkhā—"
msgstr "Eight liberations."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.192"
msgid "rūpī rūpāni passati."
msgstr "Having physical form, they see visions."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.193"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo vimokkho. (10.1)"
msgstr "This is the first liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc168"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.194"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī eko bahiddhā rūpāni passati."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving physical form internally, someone see visions externally."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.195"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo vimokkho. (10.2)"
msgstr "This is the second liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc169"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.196"
msgid "Subhanteva adhimutto hoti."
msgstr "They’re focused only on beauty."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.197"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo vimokkho. (10.3)"
msgstr "This is the third liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc170"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.198"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ "
"amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of "
"impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is "
"infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.199"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho vimokkho. (10.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc171"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.200"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘"
"consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.201"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo vimokkho. (10.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc172"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.202"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘"
"there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"nothingness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.203"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭho vimokkho. (10.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc173"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.204"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in "
"the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.205"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamo vimokkho. (10.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh liberation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc174"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.206"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.207"
msgid "Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo vimokkho."
msgstr "This is the eighth liberation."

msgctxt "dn34:2.1.208"
msgid "Ime aṭṭha dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10.8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc175"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.209"
msgid ""
"Iti ime asīti dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these eighty things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:2.1.210"
msgid "9. Nava dhammā"
msgstr "9. Groups of Nine"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2.2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc176"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.1"
msgid "Nava dhammā bahukārā … pe … nava dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr "Nine things are helpful, etc."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc177"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.2"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What nine things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Nava yonisomanasikāramūlakā dhammā, yonisomanasikaroto pāmojjaṃ jāyati, "
"pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ "
"vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati, samāhite citte yathābhūtaṃ jānāti "
"passati, yathābhūtaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ nibbindati, nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā "
"vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Nine things rooted in proper attention. When you attend properly, joy "
"springs up. When you’re joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of "
"rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, you feel "
"bliss. And when you’re blissful, the mind becomes immersed. When your mind "
"is immersed, you truly know and see. When you truly know and see, you grow "
"disillusioned. Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades "
"away you’re freed."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.4"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā bahukārā. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc178"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.5"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.6"
msgid "Nava pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgāni—"
msgstr "Nine factors of trying to be pure."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.7"
msgid ""
"sīlavisuddhi pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, cittavisuddhi pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, "
"diṭṭhivisuddhi pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, kaṅkhāvitaraṇavisuddhi "
"pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, maggāmaggañāṇadassanavisuddhi "
"pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, paṭipadāñāṇadassanavisuddhi "
"pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, ñāṇadassanavisuddhi pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, "
"paññāvisuddhi pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ, vimuttivisuddhi "
"pārisuddhipadhāniyaṅgaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The factors of trying to be pure in ethics, mind, view, going beyond doubt, "
"knowledge and vision of the variety of paths, knowledge and vision of the "
"practice, knowledge and vision, wisdom, and freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.8"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc179"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.9"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.10"
msgid "Nava sattāvāsā—"
msgstr "Nine abodes of sentient beings."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.11"
msgid ""
"santāvuso, sattā nānattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi manussā ekacce ca "
"devā ekacce ca vinipātikā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as human beings, some gods, and some beings in the "
"underworld."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sattāvāso. (3.1)"
msgstr "This is the first abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc180"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.13"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā nānattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā brahmakāyikā "
"paṭhamābhinibbattā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are diverse in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods reborn in Brahmā’s Group through the first "
"absorption."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sattāvāso. (3.2)"
msgstr "This is the second abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc181"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.15"
msgid "Santāvuso, sattā ekattakāyā nānattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā ābhassarā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and diverse in "
"perception, such as the gods of streaming radiance."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sattāvāso. (3.3)"
msgstr "This is the third abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc182"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.17"
msgid "Santāvuso, sattā ekattakāyā ekattasaññino, seyyathāpi devā subhakiṇhā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are unified in body and unified in "
"perception, such as the gods replete with glory."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sattāvāso. (3.4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc183"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.19"
msgid "Santāvuso, sattā asaññino appaṭisaṃvedino, seyyathāpi devā asaññasattā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that are non-percipient and do not experience "
"anything, such as the gods who are non-percipient beings."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.20"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo sattāvāso. (3.5)"
msgstr "This is the fifth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc184"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.21"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā "
"nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond perceptions of form. "
"With the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, they have been reborn in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.22"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭho sattāvāso. (3.6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc185"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.23"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite space. Aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamo sattāvāso. (3.7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc186"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.25"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti "
"ākiñcaññāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness. Aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they have been "
"reborn in the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.26"
msgid "Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo sattāvāso. (3.8)"
msgstr "This is the eighth abode of sentient beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc187"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.27"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso, sattā sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpagā."
msgstr ""
"There are sentient beings that have gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"nothingness. They have been reborn in the dimension of neither perception "
"nor non-perception."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.28"
msgid "Ayaṃ navamo sattāvāso."
msgstr "This is the ninth abode of sentient beings."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.29"
msgid "(3.9) Ime nava dhammā pariññeyyā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.289"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc188"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.30"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.31"
msgid "Nava taṇhāmūlakā dhammā—"
msgstr "Nine things rooted in craving."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.32"
msgid ""
"taṇhaṃ paṭicca pariyesanā, pariyesanaṃ paṭicca lābho, lābhaṃ paṭicca "
"vinicchayo, vinicchayaṃ paṭicca chandarāgo, chandarāgaṃ paṭicca ajjhosānaṃ, "
"ajjhosānaṃ paṭicca pariggaho, pariggahaṃ paṭicca macchariyaṃ, macchariyaṃ "
"paṭicca ārakkho, ārakkhādhikaraṇaṃ "
"daṇḍādānasatthādānakalahaviggahavivādatuvaṃtuvaṃpesuññamusāvādā aneke pāpakā "
"akusalā dhammā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"Craving is a cause for seeking. Seeking is a cause for gaining material "
"possessions. Gaining material possessions is a cause for assessing. "
"Assessing is a cause for desire and lust. Desire and lust is a cause for "
"attachment. Attachment is a cause for possessiveness. Possessiveness is a "
"cause for stinginess. Stinginess is a cause for safeguarding. Owing to "
"safeguarding, many bad, unskillful things come to be: taking up the rod and "
"the sword, quarrels, arguments, fights, accusations, divisive speech, and "
"lies."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.33"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc189"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.34"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What nine things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.35"
msgid "Nava āghātavatthūni:"
msgstr "Nine grounds for resentment."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.36"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me acarī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati, "
msgstr "Thinking: ‘They did wrong to me,’ you harbor resentment. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.37"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me caratī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati, "
msgstr "Thinking: ‘They are doing wrong to me’ … "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.38"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;"
msgstr "‘They will do wrong to me’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.39"
msgid "‘piyassa me manāpassa anatthaṃ acarī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They did wrong by someone I love’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.40"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ caratī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They are doing wrong by someone I love’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.41"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati;"
msgstr "‘They will do wrong by someone I love’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.42"
msgid "‘appiyassa me amanāpassa atthaṃ acarī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They helped someone I dislike’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.43"
msgid "‘atthaṃ caratī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They are helping someone I dislike’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.44"
msgid "‘atthaṃ carissatī’ti āghātaṃ bandhati."
msgstr "Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike,’ you harbor resentment."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.45"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc190"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.46"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What nine things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.47"
msgid "Nava āghātapaṭivinayā:"
msgstr "Nine methods to get rid of resentment."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.48"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me acari, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti;"
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘They did wrong to me, but what can I possibly do?’ you get rid of "
"resentment."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.49"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me carati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti;"
msgstr "Thinking: ‘They are doing wrong to me …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.50"
msgid "‘anatthaṃ me carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti;"
msgstr "‘They will do wrong to me …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.51"
msgid "‘piyassa me manāpassa anatthaṃ acari … pe …"
msgstr "‘They did wrong by someone I love …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.52"
msgid "anatthaṃ carati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They are doing wrong by someone I love …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.53"
msgid "anatthaṃ carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti;"
msgstr "‘They will do wrong by someone I love …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.54"
msgid "‘appiyassa me amanāpassa atthaṃ acari … pe …"
msgstr "‘They helped someone I dislike …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.55"
msgid "atthaṃ carati … pe …"
msgstr "‘They are helping someone I dislike …’ …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.56"
msgid "atthaṃ carissati, taṃ kutettha labbhā’ti āghātaṃ paṭivineti."
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘They will help someone I dislike, but what can I possibly do?’ "
"you get rid of resentment."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.57"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc191"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.58"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What nine things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.59"
msgid "Nava nānattā—"
msgstr "Nine kinds of diversity."

#. VAR: () → (lābhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati ­mañña­nā­nānat­taṃ) (bj)
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.60"
msgid ""
"dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ, phassanānattaṃ paṭicca "
"uppajjati vedanānānattaṃ, vedanānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saññānānattaṃ, "
"saññānānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṅkappanānattaṃ, saṅkappanānattaṃ paṭicca "
"uppajjati chandanānattaṃ, chandanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariḷāhanānattaṃ, "
"pariḷāhanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati pariyesanānānattaṃ, pariyesanānānattaṃ "
"paṭicca uppajjati lābhanānattaṃ ()."
msgstr ""
"Diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. Diversity of "
"contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings. Diversity of feelings gives "
"rise to diversity of perceptions. Diversity of perceptions gives rise to "
"diversity of intentions. Diversity of intentions gives rise to diversity of "
"desires. Diversity of desires gives rise to diversity of passions. Diversity "
"of passions gives rise to diversity of searches. Diversity of searches gives "
"rise to diversity of gains."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.61"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.290"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc192"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.62"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.63"
msgid "Nava saññā—"
msgstr "Nine perceptions:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.64"
msgid ""
"asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhārepaṭikūlasaññā, sabbalokeanabhiratisaññā, "
"aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, "
"virāgasaññā."
msgstr ""
"the perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness in food, dissatisfaction "
"with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, not-self in "
"suffering, giving up, and fading away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.65"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc193"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.66"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.67"
msgid "Nava anupubbavihārā—"
msgstr "Nine progressive meditations."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.68"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.69"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "second absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.70"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.71"
msgid "Sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.72"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā … pe … ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of "
"impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is "
"infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.73"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘"
"consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.74"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘"
"there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"nothingness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.75"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in "
"the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.76"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.77"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc194"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.78"
msgid "Katame nava dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What nine things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.79"
msgid "Nava anupubbanirodhā—"
msgstr "Nine progressive cessations."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.80"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa kāmasaññā niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the first absorption, sensual perceptions have "
"ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.81"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa vitakkavicārā niruddhā honti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the second absorption, the placing of the mind "
"and keeping it connected have ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.82"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa pīti niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr "For someone who has attained the third absorption, rapture has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.83"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpannassa assāsapassāssā niruddhā honti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the fourth absorption, breathing has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.84"
msgid "ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa rūpasaññā niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite space, the perception "
"of form has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.85"
msgid "viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākāsānañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of infinite consciousness, the "
"perception of the dimension of infinite space has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.86"
msgid "ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa viññāṇañcāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of nothingness, the perception of "
"the dimension of infinite consciousness has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.87"
msgid ""
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpannassa ākiñcaññāyatanasaññā niruddhā hoti, "
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception, the perception of the dimension of nothingness has ceased. "

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.88"
msgid "saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpannassa saññā ca vedanā ca niruddhā honti."
msgstr ""
"For someone who has attained the cessation of perception and feeling, "
"perception and feeling have ceased."

msgctxt "dn34:2.2.89"
msgid "Ime nava dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc195"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.90"
msgid ""
"Iti ime navuti dhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā "
"tathāgatena abhisambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"So these ninety things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn34:2.2.91"
msgid "10. Dasa dhammā"
msgstr "10. Groups of Ten"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="pts-cs2.3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc196"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.1"
msgid "Dasa dhammā bahukārā … pe … dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā."
msgstr ""
"Ten things are helpful, ten things should be developed, ten things should be "
"completely understood, ten things should be given up, ten things make things "
"worse, ten things lead to distinction, ten things are hard to comprehend, "
"ten things should be produced, ten things should be directly known, ten "
"things should be realized."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc197"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.2"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā bahukārā?"
msgstr "What ten things are helpful?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.3"
msgid "Dasa nāthakaraṇā dhammā—"
msgstr "Ten qualities that serve as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.4"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno, aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"First, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.5"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.6"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.1)"
msgstr "This is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc198"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.7"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu bahussuto … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is learned."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.8"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu bahussuto … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.9"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.2)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc199"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.10"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅko."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant has good friends, companions, and associates."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.11"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe … kalyāṇasampavaṅko."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.12"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.3)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc200"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.13"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu suvaco hoti sovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi "
"samannāgato, khamo padakkhiṇaggāhī anusāsaniṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is easy to admonish, having qualities that make "
"them easy to admonish. They’re patient, and take instruction respectfully."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.14"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe … anusāsaniṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.15"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.4)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc201"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.16"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu yāni tāni sabrahmacārīnaṃ uccāvacāni "
"kiṅkaraṇīyāni tattha dakkho hoti analaso tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgato, "
"alaṃ kātuṃ, alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is expert and tireless in a diverse spectrum of "
"duties for their spiritual companions, understanding how to go about things "
"in order to complete and organize the work."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.17"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe … alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.18"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.5)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc202"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.19"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu dhammakāmo hoti piyasamudāhāro abhidhamme "
"abhivinaye uḷārapāmojjo."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant loves the teachings and is a delight to converse "
"with, being full of joy in the teaching and training."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.20"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe … uḷārapāmojjo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.21"
msgid "Ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.6)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc203"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.22"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarehi "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārehi."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is content with any kind of robes, alms-food, "
"lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.23"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.24"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.7)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc204"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.25"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati … pe … kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is energetic."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.26"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.27"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.8)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc205"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.28"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu satimā hoti, paramena satinepakkena "
"samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and "
"alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.29"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.30"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo. (1.9)"
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc206"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.31"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato, ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.32"
msgid "Yaṃpāvuso, bhikkhu … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.33"
msgid "ayampi dhammo nāthakaraṇo."
msgstr "This too is a quality that serves as protector."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.34"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā bahukārā. (1.10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc207"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.35"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be developed?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.36"
msgid "Dasa kasiṇāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Ten universal dimensions of meditation."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.37"
msgid "pathavīkasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Someone perceives the meditation on universal earth above, below, across, "
"non-dual and limitless."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.38"
msgid "Āpokasiṇameko sañjānāti … pe …"
msgstr "They perceive the meditation on universal water …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.39"
msgid "tejokasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal fire …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.40"
msgid "vāyokasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal air …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.41"
msgid "nīlakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal blue …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.42"
msgid "pītakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal yellow …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.43"
msgid "lohitakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal red …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.44"
msgid "odātakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal white …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.45"
msgid "ākāsakasiṇameko sañjānāti …"
msgstr "the meditation on universal space …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.46"
msgid "viññāṇakasiṇameko sañjānāti uddhaṃ adho tiriyaṃ advayaṃ appamāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They perceive the meditation on universal consciousness above, below, "
"across, non-dual and limitless."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.47"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā bhāvetabbā. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc208"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.48"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā pariññeyyā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be completely understood?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.49"
msgid "Dasāyatanāni—"
msgstr "Ten sense fields:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.50"
msgid ""
"cakkhāyatanaṃ, rūpāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, saddāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, "
"gandhāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, rasāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"eye and sights, ear and sounds, nose and smells, tongue and tastes, body and "
"touches."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.51"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā pariññeyyā. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc209"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.52"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā pahātabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be given up?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.53"
msgid "Dasa micchattā—"
msgstr "Ten wrong ways:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.54"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, "
"micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti."
msgstr ""
"wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, "
"wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong "
"freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.55"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā pahātabbā. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc210"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.56"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā hānabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What ten things make things worse?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.57"
msgid "Dasa akusalakammapathā—"
msgstr "Ten ways of doing unskillful deeds:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.58"
msgid ""
"pāṇātipāto, adinnādānaṃ, kāmesumicchācāro, musāvādo, pisuṇā vācā, pharusā "
"vācā, samphappalāpo, abhijjhā, byāpādo, micchādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s "
"false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong "
"view."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.59"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā hānabhāgiyā. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.291"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc211"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.60"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā visesabhāgiyā?"
msgstr "What ten things lead to distinction?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.61"
msgid "Dasa kusalakammapathā—"
msgstr "Ten ways of doing skillful deeds:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.62"
msgid ""
"pāṇātipātā veramaṇī, adinnādānā veramaṇī, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī, "
"musāvādā veramaṇī, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī, "
"samphappalāpā veramaṇī, anabhijjhā, abyāpādo, sammādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; "
"avoiding speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, "
"good will, and right view."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.63"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā visesabhāgiyā. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc212"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.64"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā duppaṭivijjhā?"
msgstr "What ten things are hard to comprehend?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.65"
msgid "Dasa ariyavāsā—"
msgstr "Ten noble abodes."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.66"
msgid ""
"idhāvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti, chaḷaṅgasamannāgato, ekārakkho, "
"caturāpasseno, paṇunnapaccekasacco, samavayasaṭṭhesano, anāvilasaṅkappo, "
"passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro, suvimuttacitto, suvimuttapañño."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant has given up five factors, possesses six factors, has a single "
"guard, has four supports, has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of "
"the truth, has totally given up searching, has unsullied intentions, has "
"stilled the physical process, and is well freed in mind and well freed by "
"wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc213"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.67"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant given up five factors?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.68"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, "
"thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant has given up sensual desire, ill will, dullness and "
"drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, and doubt."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.69"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu pañcaṅgavippahīno hoti. (7.1)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has given up five factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc214"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.70"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu chaḷaṅgasamannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant possess six factors?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.71"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā neva sumano hoti na dummano, "
"upekkhako viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant, seeing a sight with their eyes, is neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.72"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "Hearing a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.73"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "Smelling an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.74"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.75"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "Feeling a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.76"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya neva sumano hoti na dummano, upekkhako viharati sato "
"sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"Knowing a thought with their mind, they’re neither happy nor sad. They "
"remain equanimous, mindful and aware."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.77"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu chaḷaṅgasamannāgato hoti. (7.2)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant possesses six factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc215"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.78"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu ekārakkho hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have a single guard?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.79"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu satārakkhena cetasā samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant’s heart is guarded by mindfulness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.80"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu ekārakkho hoti. (7.3)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has a single guard."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc216"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.81"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu caturāpasseno hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have four supports?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.82"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, "
"saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodeti."
msgstr ""
"After reflection, a mendicant uses some things, endures some things, avoids "
"some things, and gets rid of some things."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.83"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu caturāpasseno hoti. (7.4)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has four supports."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc217"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.84"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu paṇunnapaccekasacco hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And how has a mendicant eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.85"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno yāni tāni puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ puthupaccekasaccāni, "
"sabbāni tāni nunnāni honti paṇunnāni cattāni vantāni muttāni pahīnāni "
"paṭinissaṭṭhāni."
msgstr ""
"Different ascetics and brahmins have different idiosyncratic interpretations "
"of the truth. A mendicant has dispelled, eliminated, thrown out, rejected, "
"let go of, given up, and relinquished all these."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.86"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu paṇunnapaccekasacco hoti. (7.5)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc218"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.87"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant totally given up searching?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.88"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmesanā pahīnā hoti, bhavesanā pahīnā hoti, "
"brahmacariyesanā paṭippassaddhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they’ve given up searching for sensual pleasures, for continued "
"existence, and for a spiritual path."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.89"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti. (7.6)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has totally given up searching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc219"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.90"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu anāvilasaṅkappā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant have unsullied intentions?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.91"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno kāmasaṅkappo pahīno hoti, byāpādasaṅkappo pahīno hoti, "
"vihiṃsāsaṅkappo pahīno hoti."
msgstr "It’s when they’ve given up sensual, malicious, and cruel intentions."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.92"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu anāvilasaṅkappo hoti. (7.7)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has unsullied intentions."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc220"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.93"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant stilled the physical process?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.94"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.95"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti. (7.8)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has stilled the physical process."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc221"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.96"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttacitto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant well freed in mind?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.97"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti, "
"mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant’s mind is freed from greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.98"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttacitto hoti. (7.9)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is well freed in mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc222"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.99"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttapañño hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant well freed by wisdom?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.100"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ‘rāgo me pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant understands: ‘I’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion, "
"cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them, so "
"they’re unable to arise in the future.’"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.101"
msgid "‘Doso me pahīno … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.102"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.103"
msgid "‘Moho me pahīno … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.104"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.105"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu suvimuttapañño hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant’s mind is well freed by wisdom."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.106"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā duppaṭivijjhā. (7.10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc223"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.107"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā uppādetabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be produced?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.108"
msgid "Dasa saññā—"
msgstr "Ten perceptions:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.109"
msgid ""
"asubhasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhārepaṭikūlasaññā, sabbalokeanabhiratisaññā, "
"aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, "
"virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā."
msgstr ""
"the perceptions of ugliness, death, repulsiveness in food, dissatisfaction "
"with the whole world, impermanence, suffering in impermanence, not-self in "
"suffering, giving up, fading away, and cessation."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.110"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā uppādetabbā. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc224"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.111"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā abhiññeyyā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be directly known?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.112"
msgid "Dasa nijjaravatthūni—"
msgstr "Ten grounds for wearing away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.113"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhissa micchādiṭṭhi nijjiṇṇā hoti."
msgstr "For one of right view, wrong view is worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.114"
msgid ""
"Ye ca micchādiṭṭhipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, te cassa "
"nijjiṇṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong view are "
"worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.115"
msgid "Sammāsaṅkappassa micchāsaṅkappo … pe …"
msgstr "For one of right intention, wrong intention is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.116"
msgid "sammāvācassa micchāvācā …"
msgstr "For one of right speech, wrong speech is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.117"
msgid "sammākammantassa micchākammanto …"
msgstr "For one of right action, wrong action is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.118"
msgid "sammāājīvassa micchāājīvo …"
msgstr "For one of right livelihood, wrong livelihood is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.119"
msgid "sammāvāyāmassa micchāvāyāmo …"
msgstr "For one of right effort, wrong effort is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.120"
msgid "sammāsatissa micchāsati …"
msgstr "For one of right mindfulness, wrong mindfulness is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.121"
msgid "sammāsamādhissa micchāsamādhi …"
msgstr "For one of right immersion, wrong immersion is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.122"
msgid "sammāñāṇassa micchāñāṇaṃ nijjiṇṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "For one of right knowledge, wrong knowledge is worn away. …"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.123"
msgid "Sammāvimuttissa micchāvimutti nijjiṇṇā hoti."
msgstr "For one of right freedom, wrong freedom is worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.124"
msgid ""
"Ye ca micchāvimuttipaccayā aneke pāpakā akusalā dhammā sambhavanti, te cassa "
"nijjiṇṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"And the many bad, unskillful qualities that arise because of wrong freedom "
"are worn away."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.125"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā abhiññeyyā. (9)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.292"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc225"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.126"
msgid "Katame dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā?"
msgstr "What ten things should be realized?"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.127"
msgid "Dasa asekkhā dhammā—"
msgstr "Ten qualities of an adept:"

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.128"
msgid ""
"asekkhā sammādiṭṭhi, asekkho sammāsaṅkappo, asekkhā sammāvācā, asekkho "
"sammākammanto, asekkho sammāājīvo, asekkho sammāvāyāmo, asekkhā sammāsati, "
"asekkho sammāsamādhi, asekkhaṃ sammāñāṇaṃ, asekkhā sammāvimutti."
msgstr ""
"an adept’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right "
"livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right "
"knowledge, and right freedom."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.129"
msgid "Ime dasa dhammā sacchikātabbā. (10)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc226"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.130"
msgid ""
"Iti ime satadhammā bhūtā tacchā tathā avitathā anaññathā sammā tathāgatena "
"abhisambuddhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"So these hundred things that are true, real, and accurate, not unreal, not "
"otherwise were rightly awakened to by the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.131"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā sāriputto."
msgstr "This is what Venerable Sāriputta said."

msgctxt "dn34:2.3.132"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what Sāriputta said."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.133"
msgid "Dasuttarasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.134"
msgid "Pāthikavaggo niṭṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.293"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc227"></a>
#. VAR: Pāthiko ca udumbaraṃ → pāṭikañca udumbaraṃ (s1-3, km) | pāṭi­kodum­barī­ceva (pts1)
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.135"
msgid "Pāthiko ca udumbaraṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.136"
msgid "cakkavatti aggaññakaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.137"
msgid "Sampasādanapāsādaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.138"
msgid "mahāpurisalakkhaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc228"></a>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.139"
msgid "Siṅgālāṭānāṭiyakaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.140"
msgid "saṅgīti ca dasuttaraṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.141"
msgid "Ekādasahi suttehi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.142"
msgid "pāthikavaggoti vuccati."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.143"
msgid "Pāthikavaggapāḷi niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.144"
msgid "Tīhi vaggehi paṭimaṇḍito sakalo"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "dn34:2.3.145"
msgid "dīghanikāyo samatto."
msgstr "The Long Discourses are completed."
